# API Handling Rules

## Always Use the Axios Instance
```ts
// ✅ GOOD
import api from '../api/axiosInstance';
const data = await api.get('/users');

// ❌ BAD — raw fetch or direct axios import
const data = await fetch('/users');
```

## Encapsulate Calls in Service Functions
```ts
// src/services/authService.ts ✅
export const login = async (credentials: LoginPayload): Promise<AuthResponse> => {
  try {
    const { data } = await api.post('/auth/login', credentials);
    return data;
  } catch (error) {
    throw error;
  }
};

// ❌ BAD — API call inside a component
const MyScreen = () => {
  useEffect(() => { axios.get('/users'); }, []);
};
```

## Error Handling
- Always wrap async calls in `try/catch` or `.catch()`.
- Never swallow errors silently.
